// âš¡ Time & Space Complexity
// ðŸ” Time Complexity: O(n log n) in all cases (best, average, worst)

// ðŸ“¦ Space Complexity: O(n) â€” extra space needed for merging arrays

// âœ… Why Use Merge Sort?
// âœ” Always performs in O(n log n) time
// âœ” Great for sorting linked lists or large datasets
// âœ” Stable sort (maintains the order of equal elements)
// âœ” Simple recursive logic

// ðŸ§© Fun Fact: Merge Sort was invented by John von Neumann in 1945!

